Text: That should do for the time being...
But what do I do next...

All manner of thoughts about her father, her home,
and what is to come, swirl in Rose's head.

It all becomes a tangled mess that throws her mind
into disarray.

Her motives notwithstanding, Rose is now a fugitive
wanted for murdering the King of Oriana. She has no
intention of denying this nor of dying to flee from
the consequences.

She will bear the responsibility for killing her
father and her duties as a princess—all of it.
But it's all too much for her.

Perhaps I'll return to the capital, meet with the
factions opposed to Perv...

The more her thoughts race, the more the anxiety
makes her tremble. Obligation and pressure crush
the resolve and faith within her.

She may not know where this will lead her, but she
has to keep moving forward regardless.
Just as she starts on her way...
You have two choices.
Huh?!

Rose turns around and sees an elf with gold hair,
blue eyes, and beautifully sculpted features.
Choices, you say?

You can fight alone...or you can fight alongside us,
the Shadow Garden. But you have to choose.
*gasp*

Rose and the Shadow Garden share a common foe.
That does not necessarily mean they are on the same
side, but it is also true that her options are few.

(They will be coming for me soon. If I'm going to do
this alone, I'll need somewhere to hide, and the
mountains are likely my only option...)
(No, I suppose there's also the Lawless City.)

She is now wanted for murdering the King of Oriana.
Even in the Lawless City, people will come seeking
to claim the bounty on her head.
Can you...save the Oriana Kingdom?

Right now, we have no reason to act on your behalf.
If you want to save your country, show us your worth.
Worth...?
Yours, and that of the Oriana Kingdom.
...Can you truly save my kingdom?
That depends upon you.

Alpha's reply is succinct, simply presenting the
choices, as they hold no direction or assistance.
It is up to Rose to find her own answer.

...Is Slayer—no, Shadow—the leader of your
organization?
...He is.

Images of the one who rescued Rose as a child and
tirelessly fought evil flash through her mind.
...Forgive me, Father.
...Then my blade is yours.

With that, Rose makes her choice to believe in
Shadow.

Iris and Shadow share an intense gaze atop the train
as it barrels along the tracks.
What are you?
I said...what are you?!

Shadow. That name and this form are my truth.
Anything else is but a diversion within a deception.
Grr!
Magic surging, Iris charges forth with her blade.

And yet Shadow simply bats the attack aside with
his crowbar.
Ngh...!
Beatrix aims a slice at him from behind.
I'm Beatrix. Have we met before?

Can't say. But I would never forget a foe that puts
up a good fight.
Are the two of you worth remembering?
*gasp*
Shadow leaps down to the river below.

Allow me to show you a trick I picked up from a
witch.
What?!
Huh?!
This is a vampire technique...!
Is there nothing he can't do?!

Iris runs along the water's surface, swatting aside
the secret technique.
Haaaah!!!
Her burst shoots out toward Shadow.
However...
all it pierces is a spout of water.
The magic passes over a bridge...
where Shadow appears.
Normal water doesn't conduct magic very well...
Iris hacks down at him from behind.
But he spins and dodges the attack.
*gasp*
Shadow alters his stance and kicks Iris away.
Grr!
She splashes into the river.
Whoa?!
Now what?!
Somebody fell!
Shadow lands on the bridge.
Beatrix is on him as soon as he does so.

He observes her movements, optimizing his evasive
maneuvers.

Beatrix has her blade raised overhead...but she
abruptly sheathes it.
*gasp*
A shrill sound rings out a moment later...

and Shadow's crowbar is cleaved in two by a keen
slash delivered straight from the scabbard.

Beatrix follows up immediately with a thrust which
Shadow parries by a hair's breadth.

She keeps up the pressure even further, but this is
repelled by his ebony blade.

The progression of the battle leads them toward the
clock tower.

Back at the river, Iris groggily rises from where
she lay curled.
Shadow...!
Annerose smiles sadly.
Hope to see you again, Mundane.

Beatrix's attacks keep coming with nary a pause
between.
But Shadow wards them all off with fluid movements.
Heh...!
Beatrix fires off a flash.
I've figured you out.
Well done.
I'd say you're nearly as skilled as I am with a sword.

If only your use of magic wasn't so abysmally
crude. Such a shame.
Let me show you how power is properly—
Haaaaaah!!!

Iris bears down on Shadow, pouring her soul into
the attack.
What?!

However, Shadow merely reaches up and catches it in
his bare hand.
Are both sisters nothing more than rabid dogs?

He clenches his fist, and the beam bursts into
nothingness.
What the...?!

Shadow changes stances and shoves the staggering
Beatrix.
*gasp*
I cannot be defeated with borrowed power.
Beatrix.
*gasp*

I'll sacrifice myself to keep him still. Then you use
that opening...!

This is resolve Beatrix can understand, and so the
two of them face Shadow, fire in their eyes.
Very well. Come and try me.
Thunder claps at that moment.
Graaaaaah!!!
